EHD can be very devastating to deer herds. The
disease is closely related to Bluetongue virus
that most often is known to affect cattle. EHD can affect cattle as well.
There are many farmed cervid herd in the United
States. It could have a large impact this year on
wild herds as well as some captive herds. It
should be a reportable disease in every state. � Mod.TG]
